content.description: Crux is pulling your foot up to set up the lock off! Try not to cheat pull off the ground then get the left foot high.
content.location: On the south facing part of the boulder in the center of the face there is a pretty obvious head high crimp. Use this for your right hand, and a small but solid  crimp for your left hadn at about chest level. With your right foot pasted somehow get that left foot up and lock it off.

content.description: Crux is the first move but feet are surprisingly finicky and top out is not a gimme.
content.location: Start with right hand (or left)  in the super obvious pocket and left hand (or right) on the two part side pull (used as a right hand for 'Data and Picard'). It seems there may be a few top out options by my FA trended right a little bit (3-4 feet) to the good seam before the lip and topped out there.

content.description: Crux is the first couple moves getting to the depression above. I have a feeling this one is going to have a lot of different sequences.
content.location: Data and Picard is starts on north west corner of the boulder on a jug left hand and a cool right and two part side pull. Go straight up through the depression.

content.description: Not really sure of the grade on this one. Its almost really cool but its too dabby and dumpy to be great. A move of compression leads to better holds.
content.location: On the far right side of the boulder where it joins the cliff you can force one more line out of this boulder. Start with right hand on jugs at the corner and left hand on the opposing sloper. Go up.
